author: Phil Thompson
title: Elena Delle Donne top vote-getter on All-WNBA team
text:
Elena Delle Donne top vote-getter on All-WNBA team Game 1: Sky 77, Fever 72 Chris Sweda / Chicago Tribune 
Chicago Sky guard Elena Delle Donne looks to make a move against the Indiana Fever in the first half. 
Chicago Sky guard Elena Delle Donne looks to make a move against the Indiana Fever in the first half. (Chris Sweda / Chicago Tribune) Phil Thompson Contact Reporter Chicago Tribune Elena Delle Donne top vote-getter on All-WNBA team 
Elena Delle Donne has been voted unanimously to the All-WNBA first team. The Sky forward, who was named most valuable player earlier this season, received first-team votes from all 39 media members. 
Sky point guard Courtney Vandersloot was voted to the second team after leading the league in assists (5.8). 
Here are the results of voting for All-WNBA first and second teams. 
FIRST TEAM 
Elena Delle Donne, F, Sky -- 195 points 
Maya Moore, F, Lynx -- 188 
Tina Charles, C, Liberty -- 167 
DeWanna Bonner, G, Mercury -- 131 
Angel McCoughtry, G, Dream -- 102 
SECOND 
Candace Parker, F, Sparks -- 106 
Tamika Catchings, F, Fever -- 63 
Brittney Griner, C, Mercury -- 147 
Epiphanny Prince, G, Liberty -- 96 
Courtney Vandersloot, G, Sky -- 73
